{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "amigoscode-microservices-api-tests",
    "name": "Amigoscode Microservices — API Tests",
    "description": "Controller-level API tests for Customer, Fraud, and Notification services.\n\nMaps directly to the 25 JUnit 5 test cases in:\n- CustomerControllerTest.java\n- FraudControllerTest.java\n- NotificationControllerTest.java\n\n**Collection Variables** (edit these to match your environment):\n- `customerBaseUrl`  → http://localhost:8080\n- `fraudBaseUrl`     → http://localhost:8081\n- `notificationBaseUrl` → http://localhost:8082\n\n> ⚠️  Tests marked [MOCK ONLY] verify behaviour that only occurs when a service dependency throws — i.e., they require mocking and cannot be triggered via HTTP alone against the real running service.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "customerBaseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "fraudBaseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8081",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "notificationBaseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8082",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Customer Service",
      "description": "Endpoint: POST /api/v1/customers\nRegisters a new customer. Delegates to CustomerService which saves the customer, checks fraud, and publishes a RabbitMQ notification.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "TC-CUST-001 — Valid payload → 200 OK",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"firstName\": \"Alex\",\n    \"lastName\": \"Doe\",\n    \"email\": \"alex.doe@example.com\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{customerBaseUrl}}/api/v1/customers",
              "host": ["{{customerBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "customers"]
            },
            "description": "Valid full registration payload. Expects 200 OK with empty body."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('TC-CUST-001: Status is 200 OK', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "TC-CUST-002 — Partial payload (firstName only) → 200 OK",
